    "The results of these tests are summarized in Table 10 and some exemplary outputs are given in Appendix A. 4.",
    "We observe that GPT-4 produced two wrong lines of code, which could be fixed by putting the error message back as a prompt.",
    "Still, GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 performed comparatively well, mostly using wrong position vectors for joints relative to the bodies' reference positions.In some cases, feeding error back in a second iteration, appropriate training, improved fine tuning or vision-based inputs (with multimodal LLM) could resolve such problems in the future.Figure 5 shows a screenshot of the triple-pendulum (Example 6) and of the slider-crank mechanism (Example 6.1) created from the output of GPT-4.",
    "Note that the geometry of the slider-crank mechanism would not work for full revolutions of the crank, because the crank and conrod have the same lengths.",
    "Nevertheless, the direct extension from the triplependulum to a slider-crank mechanism has been performed correctly."
